{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.8",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 8 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:1",
      "text": "Then Baldad, the Suhite, answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:2",
      "text": "How long wilt thou speak these things, and how long shall the words of thy mouth be like a strong wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:3",
      "text": "Doth God pervert judgment, or doth the Almighty overthrow that which is just?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:4",
      "text": "Although thy children have sinned against him, and he hath left them in the hand of their iniquity:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:5",
      "text": "Yet if thou wilt arise early to God, and wilt beseech the Almighty:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:6",
      "text": "If thou wilt walk clean and upright, he will presently awake unto thee, and will make the dwelling of thy justice peaceable:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:7",
      "text": "In so much, that if thy former things were small thy latter things would be multiplied exceedingly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:8",
      "text": "For inquire of the former generation, and search diligently into the memory of the fathers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:9",
      "text": "(For we are but of yesterday, and are ignorant that our days upon earth are but a shadow)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:10",
      "text": "And they shall teach thee: they shall speak to thee, and utter words out of their hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:11",
      "text": "Can the rush be green without moisture? or sedge bush grow without water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:12",
      "text": "When it is yet in flower, and is not plucked up with the hand, it withereth before all herbs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:13",
      "text": "Even so are the ways of all that forget God, and the hope of the hypocrite shall perish:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:14",
      "text": "His folly shall not please him, and his trust shall be like the spider's web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:15",
      "text": "He shall lean upon his house, and it shall not stand: he shall prop it up, and it shall not rise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:16",
      "text": "He seemeth to have moisture before the sun cometh; and at his rising, his blossom shall shoot forth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:17",
      "text": "His roots shall be thick upon a heap of stones; and among the stones he shall abide.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:18",
      "text": "If one swallow him up out of his place, he shall deny him, and shall say: I know thee not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:19",
      "text": "For this is the joy of his way, that others may spring again out of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:20",
      "text": "God will not cast away the simple, nor reach out his hand to the evil doer:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:21",
      "text": "Until thy mouth be filled with laughter, and thy lips with rejoicing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.8.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:22",
      "text": "They that hate thee, shall be clothed with confusion: and the dwelling of the wicked shall not stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
